    "summary": "This paper demonstrates room-temperature, field-free current-induced switching of an in-plane CoFeB magnet in a Si/α-Sn(6 nm)/Ag(2 nm)/CoFeB(2 nm) heterostructure. The key claim is that the switching is mainly driven by spin-orbit torque from topological surface states of strained α-Sn, with transport and control experiments used to rule out Oersted-field, heating, and bulk-α-Sn mechanisms.",
